Mărişelu Hydro Power Plant is a large power plant on the Someşul Cald river situated in Romania.
The project was started and finished in the 1980s and it was made up by the construction of a rockfill dam 92 m high which was equipped with three hydrounits, the hydropower plant having an installed capacity of 221 MW.
The power plant generates 560 GWh of electricity per year.
